      <h1 class="section-heading">The Community Charter</h1>
      <p class="lead">
        The TGK Community is founded upon clarity, dignity, and the disciplined pursuit 
        of understanding. This Charter establishes the shared expectations that allow 
        rigorous discussion to flourish without hostility or confusion.
      </p>
    </section>

    <!-- PRINCIPLES -->
    <section class="section-block">
      <h2 class="section-heading">Core Principles</h2>

      <ul class="charter-list">
        <li><strong>Dignity:</strong> Every participant is addressed with respect, irrespective of disagreement.</li>
        <li><strong>Clarity:</strong> Contributions must be stated plainly and free of needless provocation.</li>
        <li><strong>Honesty:</strong> Claims should be sincere and corrected openly when mistaken.</li>
        <li><strong>Curiosity:</strong> Inquiry is valued above certainty.</li>
        <li><strong>Accountability:</strong> Participants accept responsibility for the tone and effect of their words.</li>
      </ul>
    </section>

    <!-- EXPECTATIONS -->
    <section class="section-block">
      <h2 class="section-heading">behavioral Expectations</h2>

      <ul class="rules-list">
        <li>Address ideas rather than individuals.</li>
        <li>Represent opposing views fairly before responding.</li>
        <li>Ask clarifying questions where required.</li>
        <li>Write with the assumption that your words endure.</li>
        <li>Offer correction without humiliation.</li>
        <li>Contribute substantively or refrain from posting.</li>
      </ul>
    </section>

    <!-- PURPOSE -->
    <section class="section-block">
      <h2 class="section-heading">Purpose of the Charter</h2>
      <p>
        This Charter is not a punitive instrument. It is a protective framework that guards 
        the integrity of discussion and preserves the quality of collective inquiry. It ensures 
        that disagreement can be conducted rigorously whilst maintaining mutual dignity.
      </p>
    </section>

